url_title: Lost Tapes | George Lincoln Rockwell, Haight-Ashbury (1966)
url_description: Gene Dealessi interviews George Lincoln Rockwell in San Francisco October 18, 1966. Having enjoyed modest success with his White Power Rally in Chicago the previous month, Rockwell was all the more reviled by the indiscreet hedonism of Bay Area Boomers ramping up for the Summer of Love. Not broadcast since it originally aired on KPFA January 2, 1967. While a palpable degree of contempt is heard at the outset, Dealessi skillfully restrains his indignation. A rare subdued and defeated Rockwell emerges as his performative provocation efforts quickly fizzle out. Particularly noteworthy is when Dealessi brings up Doc, a topic Rockwell is clearly not braced for. Special thanks to Pacifica Radio Archives for preserving this unique exchange. Due to the subject matter and the nature of this platform, comments are disabled.
